span><hr size=1> Hi all, I have know a bit about the quest for this bow(  <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=3990">everquest.allakhazam.com/...?item=3990</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> )for a while, but due to faction reasons have know that it might not be possible, although i got vuldeens tail recently i looked into it a bit more. Anyway being a ranger we have the ability to sneak and thus avoid some faction disadvantages, so it might be posible to invis, sneak and hand in vuldeens tail to the named giant and thus recieve the bow, from what i have read it would appear that this might  work. This still is not an easy task, being the giant in question may be more giants that can see invis.....<br>
<br>
 I found this on another site on a way to draw out the said giant and maybe complete the quest using invis and sneak.<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot; Found Gleed. Just didn't see him before cause he was dead all the other times I went there.<br>
<br>
Looks like to pull him, set one ogre right on the little ramp halfway up in order to get Gleed on that ramp. Ogre #2 should be just above that ramp. Get too close to Trooper Ymmedlor and he will kill you before Gleed makes any more movements to come kill #2 ogre.#3 ogre should be right by the fire pot thing closest to where Trooper Ymmedlor was. Hopefully, when # 2 ogre does his thing, Ymmedlor will move too so that you can pull from that spot and actually move Gleed near there before getting whacked.<br>
<br>
I'll let you guys figure out the rest. The idea is not to just get as much range, but rather to figure out what giant will kill the ogre first. If the ones behind you kills that ogre, than Gleed won't move much at all. It might actually take 6 ogres to get Gleed beyond that archway. After that it should be easier. I am shooting to get him halfway to the bank where if you turn that last corner, you see the bank.<br>
<br>
My ranger can safely stay invis near bank, if you dont pull em beyond that last corner, than you don't have to worry too much about giants that see invis. <br>
<br>
Anyway, once they are at that corner, last ogre will tell me when they all turn around to head back to spawn points. If you only hit Gleed, than hopefully Gleed will be last one to move back. Than all you gotta do is sneak up, hand in whip and run like hell to Wakening zone.<br>
<br>
Hope this works &quot;<br>
<br>
I thought this was interesting and would probably work with a bit of messing around. What i was wondering was if any like minded rangers that also have this tail would like to attempt this one night. Tell me what you think?<br>
Stupie.<br>
